 
***************
* Conditional Assembly Definitions

* org 1
*Normal rmb 1 Use for all but special cases below
*Tandy rmb 1 Special startup msg and ^N before Ready, Break for Tandy.
*Dragon rmb 1 Same as Tandy but different startup msg.
*
*CPUType set Normal

Tandy equ 1  (non-zero prints ^N before Ready, Break for Tandy)
Dragon equ 0 (non-zero prints Dragon startup msg)
*            (NOTE: When setting Dragon non-zero you must also)
*            ( set Tandy to non-zero.)


EDITOR  equ $01 Edit/Compile Load/Save
RUNTIM  equ $02 Interpreter minus Cordic
MATHPAK equ $04 Cordic trig Functions
FULL    equ RUNTIM+MATHPAK+EDITOR Includes all facilities

*INCLUDED set RUNTIM (RunB without cordic routines)
*INCLUDED set RUNTIM+EDITOR (Basic09 without trig)
*INCLUDED set RUNTIM+MATHPAK (normal RunB)
 ifndef INCLUDED
INCLUDED set FULL (normal Basic09)
 endc
